1
00:00:00,425 --> 00:00:05,465
This series is a work of fiction inspired
by questions that arise within the human heart.

2
00:00:05,485 --> 00:00:09,865
It is not intended to offend or pass judgment
on any beliefs, religions, or individuals.

3
00:00:10,196 --> 00:00:12,084
Hey! Joe’s here!

4
00:00:13,953 --> 00:00:15,515
Listen carefully to your heart.

5
00:00:17,195 --> 00:00:18,204
What about you, Tanrak?

6
00:00:19,925 --> 00:00:21,025
Have you ever had doubts?

7
00:00:21,336 --> 00:00:25,404
There are still things
that make me…waver.

8
00:00:25,676 --> 00:00:27,004
If one day I have to choose,

9
00:00:27,707 --> 00:00:30,385
I’d choose God over anything else.

10
00:00:30,595 --> 00:00:32,906
My dad died. My mom went to prison.

11
00:00:33,226 --> 00:00:34,555
So I ended up as a scholarship kid.

12
00:00:34,947 --> 00:00:37,515
Are you still going to ask me
why I don’t believe in God?

13
00:00:37,922 --> 00:00:41,005
I’ll pray to God for your mom.

14
00:00:50,145 --> 00:00:59,075
REPENT, THEN, AND TURN TO GOD,
SO THAT YOUR SINS MAY BE WIPED OUT
ACTS 3:19

15
00:01:09,195 --> 00:01:11,558
My mom taught me to do it like this.
We each do half the work.

16
00:01:13,605 --> 00:01:14,405
Alright.

17
00:01:17,928 --> 00:01:18,907
Kind of a shame, huh?

18
00:01:19,830 --> 00:01:21,201
School’s about to start.

19
00:01:21,735 --> 00:01:23,805
Soon everyone’s gonna be back.

20
00:01:27,135 --> 00:01:28,887
I thought you said
you weren’t making up with him.

21
00:01:30,053 --> 00:01:31,155
But you’re wearing his shirt.

22
00:01:34,402 --> 00:01:36,078
I don’t like being mad at people.

23
00:01:36,441 --> 00:01:37,509
It makes me uncomfortable.

24
00:01:40,251 --> 00:01:41,306
I see.

25
00:01:42,807 --> 00:01:44,105
Now you two are good.

26
00:01:44,838 --> 00:01:46,303
So my time’s up, huh?

27
00:02:00,665 --> 00:02:02,005
That’s time for a friend.

28
00:02:08,475 --> 00:02:09,604
Then who am I?

29
00:03:27,335 --> 00:03:27,974
See?

30
00:03:27,993 --> 00:03:29,745
I told you you’re about the same size.

31
00:03:29,768 --> 00:03:31,094
It fits perfectly.

32
00:03:31,340 --> 00:03:32,201
Yeah.

33
00:03:33,165 --> 00:03:34,102
You look good.

34
00:03:35,368 --> 00:03:37,536
So, what’s the decision?

35
00:03:37,685 --> 00:03:39,401
You’ve made up your mind, right? Hm?

36
00:03:40,379 --> 00:03:41,288
About what, Mommy?

37
00:03:41,305 --> 00:03:42,405
You know, that thing.

38
00:03:43,930 --> 00:03:44,879
Ask him.

39
00:03:44,899 --> 00:03:46,405
Don’t ask me. I don’t know.

40
00:03:52,392 --> 00:03:53,601
What are you smiling at, Barth?

41
00:03:56,484 --> 00:03:57,785
What did you want to ask me?

42
00:03:57,900 --> 00:04:00,706
You’re going on to the seminary
with Kongdech, right?

43
00:04:00,866 --> 00:04:01,604
Right?

44
00:04:02,905 --> 00:04:04,370
Oh, well…

45
00:04:04,510 --> 00:04:07,349
Come on, you’ve known each other
since you were kids.

46
00:04:07,375 --> 00:04:09,102
It’d be nice if you went together.

47
00:04:09,875 --> 00:04:12,700
Take a good look at each other now.

48
00:04:12,786 --> 00:04:15,255
After senior year, who knows
how many of you will still be left.

49
00:04:15,284 --> 00:04:16,879
Oh, don’t say that.

50
00:04:16,964 --> 00:04:18,688
These two are in it for the long haul.

51
00:04:18,707 --> 00:04:19,921
They’ve been friends since they were kids.

52
00:04:19,945 --> 00:04:21,685
So they'll keep going together, right?

53
00:04:22,358 --> 00:04:23,183
That’s enough, Mom.

54
00:04:23,215 --> 00:04:25,635
I’m just telling the truth.
No harm in that.

55
00:04:25,685 --> 00:04:26,808
Right, Tanrak, dear?

56
00:04:27,964 --> 00:04:30,007
Well, I…

57
00:04:30,251 --> 00:04:31,107
Tell me.

58
00:04:31,627 --> 00:04:34,107
I’ve got soda.

59
00:04:34,367 --> 00:04:35,275
Anyone want some?

60
00:04:35,475 --> 00:04:36,432
Yeah, I do.

61
00:04:36,459 --> 00:04:38,279
But I don’t have a cup.

62
00:04:38,309 --> 00:04:39,327
I’ll go get it.

63
00:04:39,451 --> 00:04:42,706
Barth, you can just share mine.

64
00:04:45,239 --> 00:04:46,007
Okay.

65
00:04:53,315 --> 00:04:55,905
Tanrak, are you still keeping up
with your prayers?

66
00:04:56,681 --> 00:04:57,602
Yes, I am.

67
00:04:58,276 --> 00:05:00,500
Why didn’t you come visit me during break?

68
00:05:00,530 --> 00:05:01,742
I was looking forward to that.

69
00:05:01,768 --> 00:05:03,407
The orchard was full of fruit.

70
00:05:15,055 --> 00:05:15,805
Tan.

71
00:05:16,136 --> 00:05:16,804
Hm?

72
00:05:18,608 --> 00:05:19,955
Do whatever you want, okay?

73
00:05:24,605 --> 00:05:26,202
What my parents said…

74
00:05:26,825 --> 00:05:28,625
you don’t have to take it so seriously.

75
00:05:30,065 --> 00:05:31,004
Oh.

76
00:05:32,239 --> 00:05:34,306
Yeah, it’s fine.

77
00:05:38,029 --> 00:05:39,635
And where did your rosary go?

78
00:05:40,885 --> 00:05:42,085
I haven’t seen you wearing it.

79
00:05:43,036 --> 00:05:44,605
Don’t you usually keep it on you?

80
00:05:47,139 --> 00:05:48,201
Oh. Right.

81
00:05:49,718 --> 00:05:51,355
I don’t know where I left it.

82
00:06:02,125 --> 00:06:03,356
I ran into Barth

83
00:06:04,039 --> 00:06:04,995
at the football field.

84
00:06:06,088 --> 00:06:07,278
He dropped it.

85
00:06:08,725 --> 00:06:12,007
But I don’t know
if I should give it back to you

86
00:06:12,210 --> 00:06:13,503
or give it back to him.

87
00:06:59,297 --> 00:07:00,076
Come on.

88
00:07:00,956 --> 00:07:01,910
Oh, Tanrak.

89
00:07:02,392 --> 00:07:03,675
Why are you standing here alone?

90
00:07:03,947 --> 00:07:05,801
Oh, I was going to shower.

91
00:07:08,066 --> 00:07:10,505
Put these two in my room.

92
00:07:10,524 --> 00:07:12,605
And the other two in Father’s room.

93
00:07:16,693 --> 00:07:18,404
Barth, go.

94
00:07:26,055 --> 00:07:27,300
Just put it on the table.

95
00:07:27,625 --> 00:07:28,450
Sure.

96
00:07:36,164 --> 00:07:37,005
Oops.

97
00:07:37,718 --> 00:07:38,702
Sorry.

98
00:07:48,825 --> 00:07:51,555
APPLICATION FOR ADMISSION
TO A BACHELOR’S DEGREE PROGRAM

99
00:07:55,907 --> 00:07:57,306
Sorry, I didn’t mean to.

100
00:07:57,785 --> 00:08:00,405
It’s okay. I’ll clean it up.

101
00:08:09,716 --> 00:08:11,315
You used to take football seriously?

102
00:08:11,335 --> 00:08:12,755
You even have cleats.

103
00:08:13,285 --> 00:08:15,408
I almost got into university
on a football quota.

104
00:08:18,524 --> 00:08:20,715
But I guess I was too good back then.

105
00:08:21,339 --> 00:08:24,555
Father was probably scared
I’d run off and become a footballer.

106
00:08:26,408 --> 00:08:27,515
So, yeah. That’s what happened.

107
00:08:28,685 --> 00:08:29,801
Really?

108
00:08:31,045 --> 00:08:32,404
You were really serious about it.

109
00:08:33,832 --> 00:08:34,601
Yeah.

110
00:08:36,933 --> 00:08:37,905
You know what?

111
00:08:39,565 --> 00:08:40,556
Back then,

112
00:08:41,979 --> 00:08:43,805
I used to pray to God

113
00:08:45,325 --> 00:08:46,801
to let me get that quota.

114
00:08:49,567 --> 00:08:50,607
I told Him,

115
00:08:51,895 --> 00:08:53,307
“If You let me get in,

116
00:08:54,445 --> 00:08:56,309
I’ll pray a hundred rosaries for You.”

117
00:09:00,675 --> 00:09:02,490
I asked Him to lead me
to the football field.

118
00:09:04,842 --> 00:09:06,076
But He…

119
00:09:07,075 --> 00:09:08,755
put me on this path instead.

120
00:09:17,568 --> 00:09:18,810
Do you ever miss it?

121
00:09:30,607 --> 00:09:31,604
I do miss it.

122
00:09:34,945 --> 00:09:36,195
But I don’t regret it.

123
00:09:39,371 --> 00:09:41,545
Because I know
if I hadn’t chosen to stay here,

124
00:09:43,193 --> 00:09:48,208
I’d regret that even more
for not listening to what I really wanted.

125
00:09:52,334 --> 00:09:54,207
So now, I’m thankful to Him instead

126
00:09:55,065 --> 00:09:57,402
for making my own voice
loud enough for me to hear.

127
00:10:07,075 --> 00:10:08,505
Here. It’s yours.

128
00:10:15,838 --> 00:10:16,807
What about you?

129
00:10:17,410 --> 00:10:18,955
What are you gonna do with your life?

130
00:10:20,420 --> 00:10:21,679
You already know.

131
00:10:22,893 --> 00:10:27,405
-Why ask?
-Barth, just behave yourself.

132
00:10:27,465 --> 00:10:28,702
And finish school.

133
00:10:29,585 --> 00:10:31,276
You’re already on probation, you know.

134
00:10:32,542 --> 00:10:33,506
I know.

135
00:10:34,494 --> 00:10:37,408
Father had no problem kicking Kongkit out.

136
00:10:38,050 --> 00:10:39,405
So don’t get too cocky.

137
00:10:49,545 --> 00:10:52,641
Who do you think from my class

138
00:10:53,239 --> 00:10:54,407
will continue?

139
00:10:55,065 --> 00:10:56,602
Fewer than five, for sure.

140
00:10:58,107 --> 00:10:59,707
Kongdech, definitely.

141
00:11:00,725 --> 00:11:02,302
Pong might make it.

142
00:11:03,390 --> 00:11:05,302
Ta. Thana.

143
00:11:06,515 --> 00:11:07,804
The rest…

144
00:11:09,546 --> 00:11:10,505
I don’t know.

145
00:11:18,285 --> 00:11:19,604
What about Tanrak?

146
00:11:36,375 --> 00:11:37,635
Aren’t you close to him?

147
00:11:40,137 --> 00:11:41,207
What do you think?

148
00:12:07,455 --> 00:12:08,401
What are you doing?

149
00:12:12,085 --> 00:12:13,505
Getting ready for tomorrow’s Mass.

150
00:12:13,893 --> 00:12:14,604
Oh.

151
00:12:15,873 --> 00:12:16,802
Okay.

152
00:12:17,761 --> 00:12:21,001
So, where did you go for New Year?

153
00:12:23,445 --> 00:12:25,122
I took my sibling out on the motorbike

154
00:12:25,537 --> 00:12:26,479
to watch fireworks.

155
00:12:29,147 --> 00:12:29,906
Nice.

156
00:12:30,585 --> 00:12:32,306
I was…

157
00:12:32,965 --> 00:12:34,602
stuck at school all break.

158
00:12:35,356 --> 00:12:37,007
Nothing to do. So boring.

159
00:12:38,066 --> 00:12:40,035
And I had to be with Barth the whole time.

160
00:12:41,869 --> 00:12:42,610
Right.

161
00:12:46,282 --> 00:12:48,004
That’s how your rosary ended up with him.

162
00:12:53,792 --> 00:12:55,502
Yeah, so…

163
00:12:55,719 --> 00:12:57,374
I came to thank you.

164
00:12:57,398 --> 00:12:59,099
I haven’t said thanks yet.

165
00:12:59,888 --> 00:13:00,753
No problem.

166
00:13:01,405 --> 00:13:04,253
I was trying to figure out where I put it

167
00:13:05,140 --> 00:13:06,402
or if I lent it to someone.

168
00:13:07,835 --> 00:13:09,303
But nothing's going on, okay?

169
00:13:12,747 --> 00:13:14,487
I never said anything was going on.

170
00:13:20,022 --> 00:13:21,202
Or is something going on?

171
00:13:36,515 --> 00:13:37,558
Nothing's going on.

172
00:13:41,567 --> 00:13:43,208
See you in the movie room.

173
00:14:04,710 --> 00:14:07,275
2, 3…

174
00:14:08,639 --> 00:14:09,635
4, 5.

175
00:14:11,641 --> 00:14:12,709
What is it, Tanrak?

176
00:14:15,433 --> 00:14:16,158
Huh?

177
00:14:18,556 --> 00:14:20,488
The rosary I lent you.

178
00:14:20,707 --> 00:14:22,503
Kongdech returned it to me.

179
00:14:23,096 --> 00:14:24,305
I think

180
00:14:25,976 --> 00:14:27,601
he must be suspicious about us.

181
00:14:29,007 --> 00:14:30,507
Calm down. It’s nothing.

182
00:14:31,655 --> 00:14:32,807
What if he tells Father?

183
00:14:35,998 --> 00:14:37,075
You think he’d tell Father?

184
00:14:39,644 --> 00:14:41,705
Barth, we’re screwed.

185
00:14:46,535 --> 00:14:48,905
It’s just a rosary.
People can borrow those, right?

186
00:14:49,935 --> 00:14:50,756
Right?

187
00:14:51,697 --> 00:14:52,608
It’s nothing.

188
00:14:53,143 --> 00:14:54,087
Just let it go for now.

189
00:14:55,269 --> 00:14:56,005
Okay?

190
00:14:57,950 --> 00:14:59,100
Don't get too worked up.

191
00:14:59,952 --> 00:15:00,807
It’s nothing.

192
00:15:02,149 --> 00:15:06,604
But I think lately,
we’ve been too obvious.

193
00:15:10,055 --> 00:15:11,703
I’m acting the same as always.

194
00:15:14,065 --> 00:15:15,195
No one’s gonna know.

195
00:15:16,325 --> 00:15:17,401
Don’t stress.

196
00:15:19,675 --> 00:15:20,604
It’s nothing.

197
00:15:21,257 --> 00:15:22,005
Yeah.

198
00:15:22,787 --> 00:15:24,715
We should still be careful.

199
00:15:26,685 --> 00:15:28,107
I don’t want to draw attention.

200
00:15:30,555 --> 00:15:31,407
Okay?

201
00:15:31,897 --> 00:15:32,709
Okay.

202
00:15:35,345 --> 00:15:36,405
Don’t worry too much.

203
00:15:36,475 --> 00:15:37,398
Calm down.

204
00:15:37,835 --> 00:15:38,802
It’s nothing.

205
00:15:39,365 --> 00:15:41,106
I said we should be careful.

206
00:15:41,325 --> 00:15:42,956
No one’s here.

207
00:15:49,175 --> 00:15:51,002
I was the first one in Master Phak’s room.

208
00:15:52,066 --> 00:15:53,002
You’re bragging.

209
00:15:53,713 --> 00:15:54,804
I’m serious.

210
00:15:55,205 --> 00:15:56,482
I even found cleats in there.

211
00:15:59,096 --> 00:16:02,008
So, if you were Master Phak,
what would you do?

212
00:16:04,349 --> 00:16:06,082
I think I’d keep playing football.

213
00:16:07,107 --> 00:16:08,915
No matter who says it’s right or wrong.

214
00:16:11,016 --> 00:16:11,707
Really?

215
00:16:12,435 --> 00:16:13,607
But I think

216
00:16:13,793 --> 00:16:15,102
he’s already made his choice.

217
00:16:15,915 --> 00:16:16,804
You think so?

218
00:16:17,124 --> 00:16:19,115
If it were you,
would you really give up your dream?

219
00:16:19,140 --> 00:16:20,305
Oh, Kongdech.

220
00:16:24,567 --> 00:16:25,407
You…

221
00:16:25,977 --> 00:16:26,955
can sit here.

222
00:16:30,761 --> 00:16:32,004
Help me…

223
00:16:32,604 --> 00:16:34,303
make some leaves.

224
00:16:36,451 --> 00:16:37,804
Okay. How do I do it?

225
00:16:39,414 --> 00:16:41,192
Fold it like this.

226
00:16:41,223 --> 00:16:43,604
So it comes out… like

227
00:16:44,025 --> 00:16:45,407
(Wanna talk outside?)

228
00:16:48,745 --> 00:16:49,835
(Later.)

229
00:16:53,079 --> 00:16:54,347
So it looks like this.

230
00:16:57,223 --> 00:16:58,152
(When?)

231
00:17:00,796 --> 00:17:01,592
Like this?

232
00:17:01,822 --> 00:17:03,001
Yeah, like that.

233
00:17:04,328 --> 00:17:07,507
Barth, can you cut this for me?

234
00:17:12,105 --> 00:17:12,909
How do I cut it?

235
00:17:12,915 --> 00:17:14,915
MUSIC ROOM

236
00:17:16,915 --> 00:17:17,805
Cut it like this.

237
00:17:18,765 --> 00:17:19,905
Am I doing this right?

238
00:17:20,958 --> 00:17:21,905
Let me see.

239
00:17:22,463 --> 00:17:23,602
No, it's like this.

240
00:17:26,225 --> 00:17:28,401
No, you need to layer them.

241
00:17:29,825 --> 00:17:31,285
No, like this.

242
00:17:32,001 --> 00:17:33,687
It needs to twist around.

243
00:17:40,465 --> 00:17:42,875
JUST TALK?

244
00:17:46,364 --> 00:17:47,105
Got it?

245
00:17:48,025 --> 00:17:48,907
All good, right?

246
00:17:49,215 --> 00:17:50,004
Yep.

247
00:17:50,912 --> 00:17:52,005
Do I cut this too?

248
00:17:52,287 --> 00:17:53,505
Yeah, cut it too.

249
00:18:03,125 --> 00:18:04,204
Looks good.

250
00:18:05,905 --> 00:18:06,756
This one.

251
00:18:44,285 --> 00:18:47,608
There is a truth I want you to know

252
00:18:48,055 --> 00:18:51,307
Meanings many words seem to hold

253
00:18:51,695 --> 00:18:54,875
No matter how beautiful they may be

254
00:18:54,905 --> 00:18:58,635
BARTH TANRAK

255
00:18:59,106 --> 00:19:02,376
Everything I do for you

256
00:19:02,811 --> 00:19:06,078
May reflect what my heart holds true

257
00:19:06,536 --> 00:19:09,505
Maybe my eyes already show

258
00:19:09,528 --> 00:19:12,505
The feelings in my heart that flow

259
00:19:12,945 --> 00:19:19,808
But do you know it's so much more?

260
00:19:20,250 --> 00:19:25,802
Things I would like to give to you

261
00:19:27,010 --> 00:19:28,888
I’d gather every star

262
00:19:28,910 --> 00:19:32,484
To show all the love I have for you

263
00:19:32,825 --> 00:19:34,604
And make every song belong to you

264
00:19:34,625 --> 00:19:36,435
WANNA HEAR YOU SING EVERY DAY

265
00:19:36,467 --> 00:19:41,902
To tell you I love you
more than words could say

266
00:19:42,047 --> 00:19:43,555
Through seasons change

267
00:19:43,855 --> 00:19:45,945
I'll spend with you
my every single breath

268
00:19:45,985 --> 00:19:50,235
WANNA HEAR YOU SING EVERY DAY
WHAT'S YOUR FAVORITE NOTE?
YOU'RE MY FAVORITE NOTE

269
00:19:50,272 --> 00:19:53,205
No words can replace

270
00:19:53,786 --> 00:19:59,702
What my heart means
when it says I love you

271
00:20:00,445 --> 00:20:04,607
Let this love song speak for my heart

272
00:20:04,888 --> 00:20:07,771
Which belongs only to you

273
00:20:08,547 --> 00:20:14,487
Let it be the promise of our love
until the time is through

274
00:20:20,476 --> 00:20:21,665
I’d gather every star

275
00:20:21,705 --> 00:20:26,275
EVER SINCE I MET YOU,
LOVE SONGS SOUND MUCH SWEETER

276
00:20:26,356 --> 00:20:29,753
And make every song belong to you

277
00:20:29,787 --> 00:20:35,303
To tell you I love you
more than words could say

278
00:20:35,545 --> 00:20:38,075
HOW WAS YOUR DAY?

279
00:20:38,109 --> 00:20:43,278
I'll spend with you
my every single breath

280
00:20:43,829 --> 00:20:46,656
No words can replace

281
00:20:47,303 --> 00:20:54,825
What my heart means
when it says I love you

282
00:20:54,865 --> 00:20:56,875
TAN KHAM WA RAK

283
00:22:23,202 --> 00:22:24,088
Hey, hurry up.

284
00:22:24,315 --> 00:22:26,906
Disc two’s about to start.
If you're slow, I’m not waiting.

285
00:22:49,545 --> 00:22:52,395
CAN WE MEET DURING MOVIE TIME? — TRAB

286
00:23:33,145 --> 00:23:35,755
N.A.T.
SECOND HALF OLD BUILDING.
STORAGE ROOM — NAT

287
00:23:38,056 --> 00:23:39,602
That name suits you.

288
00:23:47,651 --> 00:23:48,404
Hey.

289
00:24:06,622 --> 00:24:07,503
I’m tired.

290
00:24:11,875 --> 00:24:13,001
Me too.

291
00:24:13,336 --> 00:24:14,604
We walked all this way.

292
00:24:17,112 --> 00:24:18,306
I mean…

293
00:24:21,355 --> 00:24:23,202
I’m tired of hiding us.

294
00:24:34,016 --> 00:24:35,208
Is it worth it, then?

295
00:24:45,473 --> 00:24:46,303
Not yet.

296
00:24:52,937 --> 00:24:54,079
Still not worth it.

297
00:25:17,495 --> 00:25:18,476
Worth it now?

298
00:25:19,575 --> 00:25:20,399
Hm?

299
00:26:07,016 --> 00:26:07,801
Barth.

300
00:26:21,023 --> 00:26:21,758
Barth.

301
00:26:40,262 --> 00:26:40,970
Shit!

302
00:27:54,805 --> 00:27:55,756
He's gone.

303
00:28:00,295 --> 00:28:01,158
You go.

304
00:28:06,361 --> 00:28:07,505
Are you okay?

305
00:28:07,575 --> 00:28:08,550
Just go.

306
00:28:41,386 --> 00:28:42,085
Tanrak.

307
00:28:53,669 --> 00:28:54,902
Is the movie over?

308
00:28:59,161 --> 00:29:00,025
Not yet.

309
00:29:02,345 --> 00:29:05,507
I just remembered I forgot something.

310
00:29:10,695 --> 00:29:12,005
Is everything okay?

311
00:29:15,685 --> 00:29:16,608
Everything’s fine.

312
00:29:20,435 --> 00:29:22,559
About Brother Joe’s activity next week,

313
00:29:23,422 --> 00:29:25,279
let me know if you need anything.

314
00:29:29,125 --> 00:29:29,955
Yes, Father.

315
00:30:28,522 --> 00:30:30,075
But the question is,

316
00:30:30,796 --> 00:30:34,555
does every kind of love
lead us closer to Him?

317
00:30:35,527 --> 00:30:37,604
Some love makes us sacrifice.

318
00:30:37,989 --> 00:30:41,300
Some love makes us
want to become better people.

319
00:30:42,235 --> 00:30:45,555
But some love makes us hide.

320
00:30:46,305 --> 00:30:47,702
It makes us afraid.

321
00:30:48,124 --> 00:30:49,502
It makes us feel guilty.

322
00:30:49,775 --> 00:30:51,253
But are you happy?

323
00:30:57,616 --> 00:31:01,109
If some feelings make you feel bad,

324
00:31:01,465 --> 00:31:03,065
is that wrong, Father?

325
00:31:03,549 --> 00:31:05,105
Sometimes it isn't wrong.

326
00:31:05,915 --> 00:31:07,503
But it makes you afraid.

327
00:31:08,275 --> 00:31:09,802
Afraid you'll do wrong.

328
00:31:12,913 --> 00:31:15,502
I want to be in heaven with my parents.

329
00:31:15,654 --> 00:31:17,306
Your life is good, isn’t it?

330
00:31:18,555 --> 00:31:20,155
If one day I have to choose,

331
00:31:22,130 --> 00:31:24,795
I’d choose God over anything else.

332
00:31:46,505 --> 00:31:49,802
When we feel we must hide from God's gaze,

333
00:31:50,493 --> 00:31:53,204
it may not be because He doesn't love us.

334
00:31:54,299 --> 00:31:57,687
It may be because our hearts are confused.

335
00:32:21,855 --> 00:32:22,653
Hello.

336
00:33:54,285 --> 00:33:55,291
Hello, boys.

337
00:33:55,968 --> 00:33:57,401
-Hello.
-Hi.

338
00:33:57,448 --> 00:33:58,401
Are you tired?

339
00:33:58,475 --> 00:33:59,302
Not really.

340
00:33:59,337 --> 00:34:00,303
Not really?

341
00:34:01,201 --> 00:34:02,303
Okay.

342
00:34:03,085 --> 00:34:05,804
Welcome to the Shine of Grace Foundation.

343
00:34:06,530 --> 00:34:07,805
Come on in with me.

344
00:34:11,942 --> 00:34:14,650
Here, we’re committed to taking in
young people who lack opportunities

345
00:34:14,679 --> 00:34:16,085
and have no one to turn to.

346
00:34:16,239 --> 00:34:18,082
We welcome them into God’s embrace

347
00:34:18,848 --> 00:34:20,705
to help heal the wounds of their past

348
00:34:21,106 --> 00:34:24,204
and turn loneliness
into a sense of self-worth.

349
00:34:25,867 --> 00:34:30,807
Okay, now I’ll have each of the seniors
introduce themselves.

350
00:34:30,825 --> 00:34:33,355
Everyone will do a signature pose too.

351
00:34:33,935 --> 00:34:35,302
Let’s start with the first one.

352
00:34:36,245 --> 00:34:38,707
My name is Tanrak.

353
00:34:40,659 --> 00:34:41,808
This is Tanrak.

354
00:34:42,414 --> 00:34:43,405
Next.

355
00:34:44,015 --> 00:34:46,103
My name is Kongdech.

356
00:34:49,900 --> 00:34:52,235
Let’s count
how many beads are on a rosary.

357
00:34:52,814 --> 00:34:53,602
See?

358
00:34:54,585 --> 00:34:57,543
Mine has 53 beads in total.

359
00:35:11,260 --> 00:35:12,707
Will you come again?

360
00:35:14,519 --> 00:35:15,685
Of course I will.

361
00:35:16,072 --> 00:35:17,303
Why do you ask? Hm?

362
00:35:18,660 --> 00:35:20,602
You’re kind, just like Brother Joe.

363
00:35:21,045 --> 00:35:22,605
Wow.

364
00:35:22,977 --> 00:35:25,284
Just tell me what you want to eat.

365
00:35:26,485 --> 00:35:28,502
You’re going to be a priest, right?

366
00:35:34,890 --> 00:35:36,091
Whether I become one or not,

367
00:35:36,535 --> 00:35:38,303
I’ll still come see you.

368
00:35:38,998 --> 00:35:39,808
Here.

369
00:35:44,025 --> 00:35:44,887
I promise.

370
00:35:44,924 --> 00:35:45,805
Okay.

371
00:35:48,239 --> 00:35:50,307
All right, now that we’re done singing,

372
00:35:50,453 --> 00:35:51,684
let’s have some snacks.

373
00:35:51,822 --> 00:35:53,004
Who wants snacks?

374
00:35:53,721 --> 00:35:54,503
Let’s go.

375
00:36:01,095 --> 00:36:01,939
Tanrak.

376
00:36:03,105 --> 00:36:04,702
Who wants one? Raise your hand.

377
00:36:06,734 --> 00:36:07,599
How many pieces?

378
00:36:11,185 --> 00:36:12,555
Did everyone get snacks?

379
00:36:12,967 --> 00:36:13,460
Okay.

380
00:36:13,485 --> 00:36:15,303
Whoever jumps the highest gets a snack.

381
00:36:15,481 --> 00:36:18,090
Hey! Nice. Here, take one.

382
00:36:18,176 --> 00:36:19,007
High five.

383
00:36:19,479 --> 00:36:21,515
Mm. Go on, eat it.

384
00:36:21,890 --> 00:36:22,808
Here.

385
00:36:24,300 --> 00:36:28,107
Well, I’ve always pictured myself that way.

386
00:36:28,602 --> 00:36:29,801
A priest’s robe.

387
00:36:30,219 --> 00:36:31,105
The altar.

388
00:36:31,242 --> 00:36:33,207
And me standing there preaching.

389
00:36:33,850 --> 00:36:35,709
That’s the picture I see most often.

390
00:36:37,465 --> 00:36:42,305
if one day I have to choose,
I’d choose God over anything else.

391
00:36:50,615 --> 00:36:52,506
Wow, can you do it?

392
00:38:32,964 --> 00:38:34,005
Hello.

393
00:38:34,561 --> 00:38:36,204
This is Busaya.

394
00:38:36,673 --> 00:38:39,404
Please leave a message.

395
00:38:41,866 --> 00:38:43,804
How do I do this again? I forgot.

396
00:38:44,119 --> 00:38:45,673
Mom, I’ve shown you so many times.

397
00:38:45,697 --> 00:38:47,019
Here, I’ll record it for you.

398
00:38:47,042 --> 00:38:48,475
So you can watch it again.

399
00:38:48,564 --> 00:38:50,201
I just can’t remember.

400
00:38:50,539 --> 00:38:51,342
What do I do?

401
00:38:51,367 --> 00:38:52,639
Pick up the phone first.

402
00:38:52,665 --> 00:38:53,401
Like this?

403
00:38:53,427 --> 00:38:54,205
Yes.

404
00:38:54,333 --> 00:38:56,804
Then press the orange button.

405
00:38:57,109 --> 00:38:57,747
This one?

406
00:38:57,773 --> 00:38:58,607
Yes.

407
00:39:00,869 --> 00:39:01,811
Now say it.

408
00:39:02,804 --> 00:39:04,102
Uh, hello.

409
00:39:04,645 --> 00:39:05,915
This is Busaya.

410
00:39:07,038 --> 00:39:09,105
Please leave a message.

411
00:39:11,373 --> 00:39:12,119
That’s it.

412
00:39:12,146 --> 00:39:13,002
Now what?

413
00:39:13,027 --> 00:39:14,472
Now you can hang up.

414
00:39:14,499 --> 00:39:15,168
Hang up.

415
00:39:15,190 --> 00:39:16,300
Do I press this too?

416
00:39:16,330 --> 00:39:17,509
Yes, press it.

417
00:39:19,696 --> 00:39:20,454
That’s it?

418
00:39:20,478 --> 00:39:21,675
That’s it, Mom.

419
00:39:23,038 --> 00:39:23,942
Stop recording.

420
00:39:23,970 --> 00:39:25,503
You looked so funny, Mom.

421
00:40:03,509 --> 00:40:04,509
Ready?

422
00:40:04,885 --> 00:40:06,404
Come on, let’s take a group photo.

423
00:40:17,545 --> 00:40:19,635
A RESPONSIBLE STUDENT DISCIPLINED,
EAGER TO LEARN,

424
00:40:19,635 --> 00:40:21,635
AND DETERMINED A GOOD CHRISTIAN
SHOULD CONTINUE TO MAINTAIN…

425
00:40:21,665 --> 00:40:23,515
SCHOLARSHIP STUDENT REPORT BOOK

426
00:40:34,478 --> 00:40:36,002
Joe asked me to give this to you.

427
00:40:37,827 --> 00:40:39,001
It’s a little crumpled.

428
00:40:39,494 --> 00:40:40,309
Sorry.

429
00:40:40,709 --> 00:40:42,503
It’s okay. Thanks.

430
00:40:47,945 --> 00:40:49,875
TANRAK SAWATDIRAKKUL
HAS SERVED AS A YOUTH VOLUNTEER
MAY GOD BLESS YOU ALWAYS

431
00:40:52,585 --> 00:40:54,081
Can I get your homework book?

432
00:40:54,930 --> 00:40:56,835
Father Arnon will write in it
tomorrow morning.

433
00:40:59,385 --> 00:41:01,004
Oh, sure.

434
00:41:25,362 --> 00:41:26,555
Can I get your homework book?

435
00:41:27,257 --> 00:41:29,107
Father Arnon will write in it
tomorrow morning.

436
00:43:24,865 --> 00:43:26,915
HOW WAS YOUR DAY? / WHAT'S UP?

437
00:43:50,745 --> 00:43:57,595
WANNA HEAR YOU SING EVERY DAY
WHAT'S YOUR FAVORITE NOTE?
YOU'RE MY FAVORITE NOTE

438
00:45:27,798 --> 00:45:29,105
I was just…

439
00:45:31,745 --> 00:45:32,607
I…

440
00:45:35,995 --> 00:45:38,703
You saw the report book I wrote in,
didn’t you?

441
00:45:43,433 --> 00:45:45,305
Yes, Father.

442
00:45:47,445 --> 00:45:48,706
Think carefully.

443
00:45:49,867 --> 00:45:51,107
Reflect on it.

444
00:46:00,805 --> 00:46:02,002
I know

445
00:46:02,615 --> 00:46:05,109
there was something in there
that shouldn’t have been there.

446
00:46:06,245 --> 00:46:08,407
So you got rid of it, didn’t you?

447
00:46:12,882 --> 00:46:14,907
There’s nothing, Father.

448
00:46:24,165 --> 00:46:25,707
I believe one day

449
00:46:26,617 --> 00:46:28,876
you’ll come and tell me yourself.

450
00:48:11,045 --> 00:48:11,802
So?

451
00:48:12,915 --> 00:48:14,905
Did Father catch what you were burning?

452
00:48:19,705 --> 00:48:20,907
What are you talking about?

453
00:48:22,545 --> 00:48:24,079
Your notes with Barth.

454
00:48:24,639 --> 00:48:25,405
Well?

455
00:48:26,063 --> 00:48:27,137
Did you burn them in time?

456
00:48:30,260 --> 00:48:32,002
Did you tell Father?

457
00:48:36,625 --> 00:48:37,556
No.

458
00:48:39,059 --> 00:48:40,201
I didn’t tell him.

459
00:48:42,115 --> 00:48:43,407
You don’t have to be scared.

460
00:48:44,460 --> 00:48:46,635
I don’t like sticking my nose
into people’s business.

461
00:48:49,085 --> 00:48:50,509
And I wish I’d never found out.

462
00:48:57,655 --> 00:49:00,207
I don’t even know
what I’m more mad about, Tanrak.

463
00:49:03,891 --> 00:49:05,404
You and Barth

464
00:49:06,195 --> 00:49:07,405
hiding it from me,

465
00:49:09,785 --> 00:49:11,103
treating me like I’m stupid.

466
00:49:12,455 --> 00:49:14,109
Did you really think I wouldn’t notice?

467
00:49:17,322 --> 00:49:20,004
Or the fact that you’re not going
to seminary with me anymore.

468
00:49:21,478 --> 00:49:22,069
Kongdech!

469
00:49:22,093 --> 00:49:23,802
Either way, you betrayed me.

470
00:49:32,656 --> 00:49:34,205
I’m asking you seriously, Tanrak.

471
00:49:37,430 --> 00:49:39,207
That calling from God you hear,

472
00:49:40,925 --> 00:49:42,275
is it still as loud as it used to be?

473
00:49:47,215 --> 00:49:49,707
Don’t you want to see your parents
in heaven anymore?

474
00:49:57,645 --> 00:49:59,510
I believed we’d get ordained together.

475
00:52:13,293 --> 00:52:14,109
Tanrak.

476
00:52:17,555 --> 00:52:19,281
How long are you gonna keep avoiding me?

477
00:52:21,015 --> 00:52:23,408
What’s your excuse
for not talking to me this time?

478
00:52:26,288 --> 00:52:27,691
I have nothing to say.

479
00:52:30,555 --> 00:52:32,404
Tanrak, what’s wrong with you?

480
00:52:34,785 --> 00:52:37,404
You keep shutting me out like this.
I don’t even know what’s wrong.

481
00:52:37,491 --> 00:52:39,035
Just tell me what the hell I did wrong.

482
00:52:39,490 --> 00:52:40,505
Keep your voice down.

483
00:52:42,710 --> 00:52:44,482
Tan, just tell me. Talk to me.

484
00:52:44,530 --> 00:52:46,207
I don’t even know what I did wrong.

485
00:52:46,255 --> 00:52:47,602
I said keep it down.

486
00:52:48,805 --> 00:52:49,995
Then what do you want me to do?

487
00:52:50,149 --> 00:52:51,402
Kongdech knows.

488
00:52:59,415 --> 00:53:00,500
Who else knows?

489
00:53:01,955 --> 00:53:03,503
Who else knows? Does Father know?

490
00:53:04,705 --> 00:53:06,204
Who else knows, Tan?

491
00:53:09,571 --> 00:53:11,106
Tan, who else knows?

492
00:53:11,707 --> 00:53:13,202
Does Father know? Do our friends know?

493
00:53:14,713 --> 00:53:15,639
Tanrak, who else knows?

494
00:53:15,656 --> 00:53:16,885
I don’t know!

495
00:53:18,405 --> 00:53:19,707
I don’t know either.

496
00:53:23,716 --> 00:53:24,604
Barth.

497
00:53:27,396 --> 00:53:28,405
I’m tired.

498
00:53:30,325 --> 00:53:31,500
And I’m scared.

499
00:53:35,897 --> 00:53:37,281
And I’m not happy at all.

500
00:53:40,589 --> 00:53:41,405
Tanrak.

501
00:53:43,002 --> 00:53:44,804
I can make you happy.

502
00:53:45,342 --> 00:53:46,859
Just let go of everything for a second.

503
00:53:48,121 --> 00:53:49,580
Tan, wait. Calm down.

504
00:53:49,608 --> 00:53:50,485
Talk to me first.

505
00:53:50,750 --> 00:53:52,105
Tan, talk to me first.

506
00:53:54,179 --> 00:53:54,906
Tan.

507
00:53:55,596 --> 00:53:56,346
Barth!

508
00:54:01,745 --> 00:54:03,105
Don’t follow me.

509
00:54:03,862 --> 00:54:05,208
I’m begging you, Barth.

510
00:54:06,147 --> 00:54:07,275
Where are you going now?

511
00:54:07,995 --> 00:54:10,510
You haven’t talked to me all week.
Where else are you gonna go?

512
00:54:21,545 --> 00:54:23,805
Seriously, what the hell has God
ever done for you?

513
00:54:24,081 --> 00:54:25,604
All that praying you’re about to do.

514
00:54:26,475 --> 00:54:27,905
Talk to me instead.

515
00:54:28,645 --> 00:54:30,207
Why the hell do you keep praying?

516
00:54:30,627 --> 00:54:32,205
Has it ever f*cking helped you?

517
00:54:36,215 --> 00:54:37,502
What did you just say?

518
00:54:38,485 --> 00:54:39,253
Huh?

519
00:54:40,625 --> 00:54:41,605
I’m sorry.

520
00:54:45,105 --> 00:54:46,801
Tan, I’m sorry. I’m sorry.

521
00:54:48,185 --> 00:54:49,201
I didn’t mean it.

522
00:54:52,436 --> 00:54:54,005
I just wanted to talk to you.

523
00:54:57,315 --> 00:54:59,204
I didn’t mean it. I didn’t. I’m sorry.

524
00:54:59,995 --> 00:55:00,705
Tan.

525
00:55:03,783 --> 00:55:05,705
I really didn’t mean it.
I’m sorry. I’m sorry.

526
00:55:09,593 --> 00:55:10,505
Tanrak!

527
00:56:57,845 --> 00:56:58,705
Father.

528
00:57:03,825 --> 00:57:05,402
Can you please talk to me?

529
00:57:18,288 --> 00:57:19,103
Father.

530
00:57:21,367 --> 00:57:22,705
I’m in love

531
00:57:25,216 --> 00:57:26,805
even though I know it’s wrong.

532
00:57:29,427 --> 00:57:31,279
I tried to stop myself.

533
00:57:33,125 --> 00:57:34,502
But I couldn’t.

534
00:57:36,884 --> 00:57:38,205
I’m angry at myself

535
00:57:39,967 --> 00:57:41,909
for not being able to control it.

536
00:57:50,057 --> 00:57:50,804
Father.

537
00:57:53,039 --> 00:57:54,087
I’m scared.

538
00:57:57,465 --> 00:57:59,602
I’m scared God will reject me.

539
00:58:02,822 --> 00:58:05,303
God would never reject you, Tanrak.

540
00:58:06,205 --> 00:58:08,999
He always loves you.

541
00:58:12,737 --> 00:58:14,481
Love isn’t wrong.

542
00:58:16,225 --> 00:58:21,001
God created humans
with hearts and feelings.

543
00:58:22,161 --> 00:58:23,906
But our actions

544
00:58:24,785 --> 00:58:26,804
are what we must take responsibility for.

545
00:58:29,345 --> 00:58:31,804
I want you to think carefully

546
00:58:34,195 --> 00:58:38,109
about where this love is leading you.

547
00:58:40,349 --> 00:58:42,705
But the fact that you’re here now

548
00:58:43,700 --> 00:58:48,205
means you still want to be with Him.

549
00:58:53,195 --> 00:58:55,605
If you believe that it’s wrong,

550
00:58:56,979 --> 00:58:58,825
then you need to figure out

551
00:58:59,515 --> 00:59:02,801
how to make amends for this sin.

552
00:59:26,127 --> 00:59:27,303
If…

553
00:59:29,355 --> 00:59:30,804
If I break up with him,

554
00:59:34,553 --> 00:59:36,204
you'll forgive me, right?

555
00:59:43,355 --> 00:59:46,608
God always forgives those
who repent, Tanrak.

556
00:59:49,285 --> 00:59:51,105
You need to ask yourself

557
00:59:53,695 --> 00:59:56,207
whether you want to stay with that love

558
00:59:58,695 --> 01:00:00,404
or stay with Him.

559
01:00:05,036 --> 01:00:07,607
God always gives us a chance, Tanrak.

560
01:00:09,684 --> 01:00:11,404
But His path

561
01:00:13,039 --> 01:00:14,481
is not an easy one.

562
01:01:04,891 --> 01:01:05,703
Tanrak.

563
01:01:07,248 --> 01:01:08,305
Can we talk?

564
01:01:13,275 --> 01:01:14,476
Don’t do this, Barth.

565
01:01:21,158 --> 01:01:23,905
You know this can’t happen.

566
01:01:28,625 --> 01:01:30,085
There has to be a way.

567
01:01:31,505 --> 01:01:34,109
I still want to be with you.
I still want a future with you.

568
01:01:35,856 --> 01:01:37,856
Who cares if anyone says this is wrong?

569
01:01:37,879 --> 01:01:40,202
Even if God says it’s wrong, I don’t care.

570
01:01:40,466 --> 01:01:41,211
Barth.

571
01:01:42,633 --> 01:01:43,900
You can’t just not care.

572
01:01:45,069 --> 01:01:46,102
We’re students.

573
01:01:46,445 --> 01:01:47,503
We go to school here.

574
01:01:48,635 --> 01:01:50,007
We’re scholarship students.

575
01:01:50,817 --> 01:01:52,102
You know that.

576
01:01:59,155 --> 01:02:00,002
I don’t know.

577
01:02:02,005 --> 01:02:03,653
I don’t know anything about God.

578
01:02:06,305 --> 01:02:07,573
I only know myself.

579
01:02:09,645 --> 01:02:12,078
I know I love you.

580
01:02:23,085 --> 01:02:23,873
Tanrak.

581
01:02:27,030 --> 01:02:28,005
What about you?

582
01:02:30,405 --> 01:02:32,484
Didn’t you ever love me at all?

583
01:02:36,885 --> 01:02:38,107
I do love you.

584
01:02:39,505 --> 01:02:41,001
I love you so much.

585
01:02:47,042 --> 01:02:48,608
But what do we do with that?

586
01:02:58,404 --> 01:03:00,505
If God teaches us to love,

587
01:03:02,875 --> 01:03:04,700
but we’re not allowed to love each other,

588
01:03:06,451 --> 01:03:08,502
then what’s the point of having God
in this world?

589
01:03:45,135 --> 01:03:46,835
If this place isn’t for us,

590
01:03:51,779 --> 01:03:53,107
let's run away together.

591
01:04:38,705 --> 01:04:40,995
God probably won’t forgive me
anytime soon.

592
01:04:41,316 --> 01:04:42,355
Let’s forget about it for now.

593
01:04:42,750 --> 01:04:44,485
As long as I have you with me,
that’s enough.

594
01:04:45,705 --> 01:04:49,288
Mom, Dad, are you still waiting
for me in heaven?

595
01:04:49,405 --> 01:04:50,706
Let me take care of Tanrak.

596
01:04:50,935 --> 01:04:52,303
Whoa!

597
01:04:54,106 --> 01:04:56,007
So what are you gonna do now?

598
01:04:56,435 --> 01:04:57,687
I don’t know.

599
01:04:58,099 --> 01:05:00,625
I've spent most of my life
at Magdalene House.

600
01:05:00,838 --> 01:05:02,355
There’s food and rent to worry about.

601
01:05:02,555 --> 01:05:03,955
It's hard, huh?

602
01:05:04,119 --> 01:05:05,105
That’s just life.

603
01:05:07,105 --> 01:05:10,807
Do you think there’s a place up there
for the two of us?

